  resolve(actor) {
    return new URL(getAvatarUrl(actor));
  },
}),
```

Without `select: { columns: { avatarUrl: true } }`, `pothos-drizzle`'s `nodeSelection()` — used by `reactorConnectionHelpers` in `graphql/reactable.ts:121-130` — loads the actor row without the `avatarUrl` column, so the resolver receives `undefined` and falls back to Gravatar (`models/avatar.ts:1-3`).

Other resolvers in the same file (`iri`, `type`, `local`, `name`) declare their `select.columns` correctly.
EOF
